<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">29</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">1</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jan 1 2009</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">89</span> - <span property="pageEnd">103</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/19168838/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">19168838</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2009.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jan 1 2009</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.291085052">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keyword</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=FISP+%3D+fast+imaging+with+steady-state+precession&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">FISP = fast imaging with steady-state precession</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">Recognition of the different patterns of delayed left ventricular myocardial enhancement at cardiac MR imaging is crucial in differentiating ischemic from nonischemic disease and in narrowing the differential diagnosis in cases of nonischemic cardiomyopathy.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabp